article.headline: Old Dominion 68, Delaware 66
article.story: NEWARK, Del. -- Chris Cooper grabbed an offensive rebound and hit a layup at the buzzer in overtime to give Old Dominion a 68-66 win over Delaware on Wednesday night. Kent Bazemore, who missed the shot that Cooper rebounded, had 27 points and 12 rebounds for the Monarchs (9-8, 3-1 Colonial Athletic Association), who have won three of the past four games in the series. Richard Ross and Cooper each added 14 points for Old Dominion. A 3-pointer by Kyle Anderson gave Delaware a 57-55 lead with 40 seconds remaining in regulation, but Bazemore hit two free throws with 3 seconds left to extend the game. Bazemore hit two 3-pointers and scored Old Dominion's first nine points in overtime. There were 10 ties and 10 lead changes in the game. Anderson scored 17 points, Josh Brinkley added 16 points and 11 rebounds, and Devon Saddler had 16 points for Delaware (7-8, 3-2).
